    "body": "## Summary\n- Add `dynamic_symbolic_constraints` parameter to `Profiler.do_bench()` method, allowing users to specify concrete values for dynamic symbolic variables when benchmarking kernels with dynamic shapes.\n- Add `_substitute_dynamic_symbols()` helper method to substitute `tir.Var` in parameter shapes with concrete integer values.\n- Add comprehensive test cases for dynamic symbolic constraints functionality.\n\n## Motivation\nWhen a kernel is defined with dynamic symbolic shapes (e.g., `M = T.dynamic(\"m\")`), the profiler cannot automatically generate random tensors for benchmarking because the shape is not statically known. This PR provides a clean API to specify the concrete values for these dynamic symbols.\n\n## Usage Example\n```python\nM = T.dynamic(\"m\")\nN = 1024\nK = 1024\n\nkernel = matmul(M, N, K, block_M, block_N, block_K)\nprofiler = kernel.get_profiler()\n\n# Benchmark with specific M value\nlatency = profiler.do_bench(dynamic_symbolic_constraints={\"m\": 2048})\n\n# Benchmark with multiple dynamic symbols\nlatency = profiler.do_bench(dynamic_symbolic_constraints={\"m\": 2048, \"n\": 1024})\n```\n\n## Test plan\n- [x] `test_profiler_dynamic_symbolic_single` - Single dynamic symbolic variable\n- [x] `test_profiler_dynamic_symbolic_multiple` - Multiple dynamic symbolic variables\n- [x] `test_profiler_dynamic_symbolic_correctness` - Kernel correctness verification\n- [x] `test_profiler_dynamic_symbolic_missing_constraint` - Error handling for missing constraints\n- [x] `test_profiler_dynamic_symbolic_with_input_tensors` - Manual input tensors precedence\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Profiler supports dynamic symbolic constraints for benchmarking kernels with symbolic/variable shapes.\n  * Profiling API accepts explicit input tensors which take precedence over dynamic constraints.\n\n* **Tests**\n  * Added tests for single/multiple dynamic constraints, correctness against a reference implementation, error handling for missing/invalid constraints, and input-tensor precedence during profiling.\n\n<sub>✏️ Tip: You can customize this high-level summary in your review settings.</sub>\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
